RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INFINITE EMPIRE rated close to the early pace off the rail, pulled herself to the lead approaching the seven sixteenths pole and was rated from that point, moved clear in the three path midway on the far turn, left the turn wide and was kept in hand through the stretch. SOMEBODY LOVES ME saved ground into the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and cleared second mid-stretch. LINDA'S TAJ drew clear and angled to the inside to set the early pace, was met approaching the seven sixteenths pole and dueled at mostly even terms leaving the pole, but dropped back midway on the far turn and flattened in the lane. LIL BOSS rounded the opening turn about the three path, bid passing the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. MORE TAJ raced well off the early pace in the three and four paths and could only improve her position. MIDSUMMER NIGHTS rounded the opening turn about the five path, left the turn outside and gave chase toward the three eighths pole, but weakened into the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Infinite Empire
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,up near 7/16,pulled clear mid turn,wide 1/8,handily

TWIN CAUSE chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 36300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race Since January 25 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 25 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOONLIT SHADOW angled in and closed to the front at the thirteen sixteenths pole and raced with the early pace, came under pressure toward the three eighths, dueled clear of Far Away Love mid-stretch and held on with steady handling. DRY WELL ducked out and made sharp contact with Timeisgolden leaving the gate then steadied in tight at the heels of FAR AWAY LOVE shortly afterward, saved ground on the first turn then gave chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn about the four path and dug in to take second the final yards. FAR AWAY LOVE (ARG) raced with the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole but dropped back approaching the quarter, continued a factor through the upper stretch but flattened the final sixteenth. TIMEISGOLDEN was bumped outward and into Baci leaving the gate then pinched back, rounded the first turn off the rail, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and finished well. MISS CHAMITA raced well back saving early ground, picked up the chase nearing the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and finished well. BACI was bumped leaving the gate and steadied off the inside flank of Moonlit Shadow shortly afterward then rated close, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and flattened in the lane. After a Stewards inquiry and subsequent claims of foul by both the trainer, and rider of Timeisgolden, against the rider of Dry Well for interference at the start, the Stewards disqualified Moonlit Shadow to last place for causing a chain reaction shortly after the start.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIMMY exchanged contact with Mr. Hostler leaving the gate then closed to the front nearing the nine sixteenths pole and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the three eighths, dueled at mostly even terms from that point and dug in determinedly to eke out the nod over the game challenge of GET OFF MY CLOUD, who stalked inside and picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, dueled at mostly even terms leaving the pole and dug in gamely to the finish. CHASE LIL ME settled back two deep on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole then flattened in the four path of the far turn. MR. HOSTLER exchanged contact with Timmy leaving the gate and made contact with Leg Up shortly afterward, saved ground on the first turn, gave chase into the backstretch, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little more. REY O REYES set the early pace inside but lost action behind and nearly lost his rider into the first turn, bore out through the turn and entered the backstretch four wide, gave chase from the three eighths pole, weakened into the far turn and was eased in the lane.
